         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:meunier2013"/><citedRange>148</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Prête attention à cela!</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:couvreur1959"/><citedRange>252</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:couvreur1959"/><citedRange>252</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:couvreur1959"/><citedRange>252</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... should I have committed offences connected to the fifteen (?) <hi>śloka</hi>s, to the seven <hi>saptatikara</hi>s, connected to the hidden [objects], with the truths, with the <hi>vipravāsa</hi>s; ... intentionally ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">… should I have committed offences connected to the fifteen (?) ślokas, to the seven saptatikaras, connected to the hidden [objects], with the truths, with the vipravāsas; … intentionally …  (cf 252a)</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>649</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:couvreur1959"/><citedRange>252</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... should I have uttered a lie, harsh speech, [or] senseless talk; should I have committed offences through inertia, want of trust, [or] deception, ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">… should I have uttered a lie, harsh speech, [or] senseless talk; should I have committed offences through inertia, want of trust, [or] deception, …  (cf 252a)</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>649</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:couvreur1959"/><citedRange>252</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... should I have uttered ..., <hi>duṣthūla</hi> words; to [my] teachers, <hi>upādhyāya</hi>s [and] <hi>ācārya</hi>s, to my excellent father and mother, to those being good and faithful ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">… should I have uttered …, duṣthūla words; to [my] teachers, upādhyāyas [and] ācāryas, to my excellent father and mother, to those being good and faithful …</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>649</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:couvreur1959"/><citedRange>252</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... should I intentionally have uttered reproach, ... seen [or] heard, to others; these offences of the tongue ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">… should I intentionally have uttered reproach, … seen [or] heard, to others; these offences of the tongue …</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>649</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>404</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:meunier2013"/><citedRange>159</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:couvreur1959"/><citedRange>252</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... I remove (my sin) and confess. If there is confession for me, I will thereafter attain ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">… I remove (my sin) and confess. If there is confession for me, I will thereafter attain …  (cf 412)</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>650</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... ich beseitige (mein Vergehen) [und] lege Beichte ab.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">... I remove (my offence) [and] make confession.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>412</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>191</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
